                    <msContents>
                        <summary>A version in Chagatai Turkish of the love story of Layla and
                            Majnun, by Alî Şîr Nevâʿî of Herat, with two miniatures in the Herat
                            style. It was originally part of a Khamsa (quintet). Other manuscripts
                            from the same set are in the Bodleian Library, these were copied in
                            Afghanistan in 890 AH (1485 CE).</summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="Turkish_MS_3-item1">
                            <author key="person_22198747" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/22198747">
                                <persName type="standard">Alisher Navoiĭ, 1441-1501 </persName>
                            </author>
                            <title key="work_21374">Laylá va Majnūn</title>
                            <title xml:lang="eng" key="work_21374">Layla and Majnun</title>
                            <title xml:lang="chg" key="work_21374">ليلى و مجنون</title>
                            <incipit xml:lang="chg">اى يخشى اتيك بيل سر اغاز انجامى غه كيم يتار بر
                                اغاز <locus from="1b">(folio 1b)</locus></incipit>
                            <explicit xml:lang="chg">عصيا نيما عفو بولغاى ايين يا رب كه بو نوع
                                بولغاى امين <locus from="48b">(folio 48b)</locus></explicit>
                            <textLang mainLang="chg">Chagatai Turkish</textLang>
                            <filiation>The other four volumes from the set are Bodleian MS. Elliot
                                287, 408, 317 and 339. </filiation>
                            <note>Begins and ends as in Levend's edition.</note>
                        </msItem>
                    </msContents>
